<title>GERMANY: Germany remains opposed to IMF gold sales - Waigel.</title>
<headline>Germany remains opposed to IMF gold sales - Waigel.</headline>
<dateline>BERLIN 1997-02-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>German Finance Minister Theo Waigel said Germany remained opposed to the International Monetary Fund selling off some of its gold reserves as a means to fund aid to the world's poorest countries.</p>
<p>Asked whether this would be an issue at the G7 meeting in Berlin, he said: &quot;This is not an issue. Our position is known.&quot;</p>
<p>--Janet Northcote, Berlin Newsroom +49 30 203 8910</p>
